  "text": "The Envoy v1.31.2 TLS certificate validation implementation comprises a flexible architecture with pluggable validators. The core certificate verification logic is found in two main implementations:\n\n1. **DefaultCertValidator** (source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc, default_validator.h): Implements standard X.509 certificate validation using OpenSSL. The initializeSslContexts() method sets up certificate stores and returns verification mode flags. The doVerifyCertChain() method calls X509_verify_cert() on line 315 to perform the actual chain verification after setting up the X509_STORE_CTX. It supports multiple validation strategies including certificate hash pinning, subject public key information (SPKI) pinning, and subject alternative name (SAN) matching. The addClientValidationContext() method configures the SSL context for client certificate requirements using SSL_CTX_set_verify() on line 528.\n\n2. **SPIFFEValidator** (source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.cc, spiffe_validator.h): Implements SPIFFE-specific certificate validation. The doVerifyCertChain() method calls X509_verify_cert() on line 177 using trust bundle stores specific to each SPIFFE trust domain. The initializeSslContexts() method returns SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT to enforce peer certificate verification.\n\n**Server Certificate Validation (Client's perspective):**\n- Handled by ClientContextImpl (source/common/tls/client_context_impl.cc), which calls SSL_set_verify() on line 114 to set up server certificate verification requirements\n- The createConnection() method enforces verification of server certificates when transport socket options specify subject alternative name validation overrides\n\n**Client Certificate Validation (Server's perspective):**\n- Handled by ServerContextImpl (source/common/tls/server_context_impl.cc), which calls cert_validator_->addClientValidationContext() to configure client certificate requirements\n- The base ContextImpl class (source/common/tls/context_impl.cc) initializes SSL contexts through cert_validator_->initializeSslContexts(), which returns verification mode flags\n- Custom verification callbacks are registered via SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify() on line 181 to handle asynchronous validation\n\n**Key Verification Infrastructure:**\n- CertValidator abstract interface (source/common/tls/cert_validator/cert_validator.h) defines the contract for all validators\n- The verification modes are determined by the initializeSslContexts() methods and returned as int flags (SSL_VERIFY_NONE, SSL_VERIFY_PEER, SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT)\n- Error handling and verification result tracking occurs through ValidationResults structures and detailed_status enums\n- Utility functions in source/common/tls/utility.cc provide error reporting and certificate information extraction\n\nThe architecture allows for both synchronous and asynchronous certificate verification, with support for multiple validation strategies (trust anchor validation, certificate pinning, SPIFFE-specific validation) and comprehensive error handling and logging."
}

